Court declares impeachment of former Kogi deputy governor, Simon Achuba, null and void. The court also ruled that the subsequent nomination of Edward Onoja as the state deputy governor did not follow due process and a violation of the constitution. Justice John Olorunfemi on Wednesday faulted Achuba’s removal from office, describing it as a violation of the Constitution. More details later… VANGUARD Former Deputy Governor of Imo State, Sir Jude Agbaso, has approached the state High Court, challenging his recent impeachment and subsequent removal from office by the State House of Assembly. May 26, 2013 In "News" The Abuja Division of the Federal High Court, on Thursday, reinstated the impeached Speaker of the Kogi State House of Assembly, Hon. Momoh Jimoh Lawal. May 19, 2016 In "News" The Abuja Division of the Federal High Court, yesterday, reinstated the impeached Speaker of the Kogi State House of Assembly, Hon. MomohJimoh Lawal. May 20, 2016 In "News"